text: Rough-skinned frog may refer to: * Rough-skinned bush frog (Raorchestes glandulosus), a frog in the family Rhacophoridae endemic to the Western Ghats, India * Rough-skinned floating frog (Occidozyga lima), a frog in the family Dicroglossidae found in Bangladesh, Cambodia, China, Hong Kong, India, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, Thailand, Vietnam, and possibly Nepal * Tientai rough-skinned frog (Glandirana tientaiensis), a frog in the family Ranidae endemic to eastern China, found the Zhejiang and Anhui provinces Category:Animal common name disambiguation pages
title: Rough-skinned frog
